Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing language in social media to identify hate speech and discrimination.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the study examines the relationship between online hate speech and hate crimes in physical locations.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper discusses the development of a classification pipeline to identify discrimination in social media.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possibility as the study explores the impact of discrimination in both virtual and physical worlds.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper touches on the topic of malicious online content.
